BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Foreigner
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260715T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260715T221500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1108@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Larry Shue's 1984 farce: a painfully shy Englishman fakes spea
 king no English\, and a Georgia fishing lodge spills its secrets.\n\nLarry
  Shue's much-revived 1984 comedy\, winner of two Obie Awards. Charlie Bake
 r\, shy to the point of paralysis\, arrives at a rural Georgia fishing lod
 ge\, where a well-meaning friend passes him off as a foreigner who underst
 ands no English. The other guests promptly air their secrets\, schemes\, a
 nd romances right in front of him\, and Charlie finds unexpected nerve in 
 playing along. A community production from Renegade Theatre Company\, whic
 h donates a portion of each show's proceeds to charity.
GEO:33.7813812;-84.3632461
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Virginia-Highland Church\, 743 Virginia Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdmL5Ji8ouLElNxwnJZsqqArsGhqG
 BsGUYVxmtW1MSc3AU9KA/viewform?usp=header
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Somewhat True Tale of Robin Hood
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260716T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260716T210000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-603@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Mary Lynn Dobson's Monty Python-flavored Robin Hood spoof\, wi
 th spoon-wielding Merry Men and dessert at intermission.\n\nMary Lynn Dobs
 on's parody sends up the Robin Hood legend in full Monty Python spirit: a 
 preening hero in green\, a damsel fixated on her skin conditions\, a sheri
 ff who would rather be bowling\, and a band of Merry Men armed with spoons
  and a collective IQ of six. A cheerful "Town's Guy" keeps wandering into 
 scenes he has no business in. Walker Scott directs for Lionheart Theatre\,
  the Norcross community company\, and every ticket includes dessert at int
 ermission. Runs through July 19.
GEO:33.9421741;-84.2112431
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Lionheart Theatre\, 10 College St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/35819/production/1270020/performance/1178630
 0
END:VEVENT
