DESCRIPTION:Topher Payne's play imagines Marilyn Monroe and Elizabeth Tayl
 or alone together in a blacked-out Reno hotel\, 1960.\n\nAugust 1960: a fo
 rest fire has knocked out the power\, and in a darkened hotel Marilyn Monr
 oe and Elizabeth Taylor find themselves alone in the same room for the onl
 y time in their lives. In Atlanta playwright Topher Payne's telling\, it d
 oes not go well. DeWayne Morgan directs for Onstage Atlanta. Runs through 
