DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-554@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:A new Atlanta comedy: 100 fast-food faithful camp overnight fo
 r free combos\, and something goes wrong.\n\nA new comedy from Atlanta pla
 ywright Kira Rockwell (Oh\, To Be Pure Again): on the eve of a beloved fas
 t-food chain's grand opening\, a hundred devotees camp overnight in the pa
 rking lot to win a year of free large combos. Someone among them is stirri
 ng up trouble\, and Jade\, the brand-new store manager\, has to root out t
 he saboteur before her flock descends into chaos. Lisa Adler directs for H
 orizon Theatre. Runs through September 20.
GEO:33.7620155;-84.3525137
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Horizon Theatre\, 1083 Austin Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.horizontheatre.com/144303/145601
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Purpose
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260912T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260912T214500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-132@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Branden Jacobs-Jenkins' Tony- and Pulitzer-winning drama of a 
 Black political dynasty's reunion coming undone.\n\nThe Jaspers are a Chic
 ago dynasty of ministers\, activists\, and changemakers\, gathering for a 
 long-overdue family reunion. When a young outsider arrives with questions 
 nobody wants asked\, the family's carefully guarded secrets start to surfa
 ce over one evening. Branden Jacobs-Jenkins (Appropriate\, An Octoroon) wo
 n both the 2025 Tony Award for Best Play and the Pulitzer Prize for Drama 
 for this one\; the New York Post called it "unstoppably fierce\, funny\, a
 nd ruthless." Keith Arthur Bolden directs for the Alliance Theatre\, in a 
 co-production with McCarter Theatre Center\; runs through September 20.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164228/164279
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Philadelphia Story
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260912T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260912T220000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-594@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Philip Barry's 1939 high-society comedy: a socialite's second 
 wedding\, crashed by her ex-husband and two tabloid journalists.\n\nPhilip
  Barry's 1939 comedy of the privileged class. Tracy Lord\, headstrong daug
 hter of the Philadelphia Lords\, is set to marry a successful young snob w
 hen her ex-husband and a pair of tabloid journalists descend on the family
  estate for the wedding weekend. Barry wrote the role for Katharine Hepbur
 n\, who backed the play with her own money and carried it into the 1940 fi
 lm with Cary Grant and James Stewart. Darci Rose Wells directs for Lionhea
 rt Theatre\, where every ticket includes dessert at intermission\; runs th
 rough September 27.
GEO:33.9421741;-84.2112431
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Lionheart Theatre\, 10 College St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/35819/production/1276719/performance/1181318
 0
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Measure for Measure
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260912T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260912T214500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1452@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's problem play: a disguised duke\, a puritan deput
 y\, and a novice nun bargaining for her brother's life.\n\nThe Duke of Vie
 nna orders his city's dormant morality laws enforced\, hands power to his 
 strict deputy Angelo\, and pretends to leave town. In truth he stays\, dis
 guised as a friar\, to watch what his deputy does with the job. What Angel
 o does is sentence young Claudio to death for fornication\, and when Claud
 io's sister Isabella\, a novice nun\, comes to plead for mercy\, he names 
 a price she cannot pay with a clear conscience. The First Folio filed it w
 ith the comedies\, but its executions and moral bargaining have long earne
 d it the label of problem play. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company\, per
 formed with tavern table seating and food and drink service.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/measure-for-measure
END:VEVENT
