SUMMARY:Superior Donuts
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261024T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261024T221500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1313@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Tracy Letts's comedy-drama of a burned-out donut shop owner an
 d the young writer who shakes him awake.\n\nTracy Letts\, the Pulitzer win
 ner behind August: Osage County\, in a gentler mode: a former '60s radical
  presides over his fading donut shop in Chicago's Uptown until Franco\, a 
 bright young Black writer\, turns up looking for work and full of plans to
  fix the place. Reviewing the 2008 Steppenwolf premiere\, the New York Tim
 es's Charles Isherwood called it "insubstantial and sweet" yet "hard to di
 slike." Robby Myles directs for Authenticity Theater. Runs through October
  31.
GEO:33.7639125;-84.3509364
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:7 Stages Theatre\, 1105 Euclid Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://authenticitytheater.ludus.com/index.php?sections=events
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:i never asked for a gofundme
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T161500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-53@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:A world-premiere play: top surgery mistaken for breast cancer\
 , and a small-town GoFundMe nobody asked for.\n\nMillie and her partner Av
 ery are riding out Avery's recovery from gender-affirming top surgery in M
 illie's hometown of Mobile\, Alabama. Then a nosy evangelical family frien
 d misreads the surgery as a breast-cancer fight and launches a GoFundMe on
  the couple's behalf\, making them the talk of the town and the recipients
  of donations they never wanted. Whether to keep the money\, and what keep
 ing it would cost them\, is the question. A world premiere from Actor's Ex
 press.
GEO:33.7817253;-84.4160629
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:King Plow Arts Center\, 887 W Marietta St NW\, Suite J-107
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://purchase.actors-express.com/EventAvailability?EventId=32801
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Vanya and Sonia and Masha and Spike
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T160000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1262@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Christopher Durang's Chekhov-riffing comedy: a movie-star sist
 er\, her young boyfriend\, and a family farmhouse up for sale.\n\nChristop
 her Durang's comedy borrows its names and its moods from Chekhov\, then le
 ts them loose in present-day Pennsylvania. Siblings Vanya and Sonia have s
 pent their quiet lives in the family farmhouse\; their movie-star sister M
 asha blows in for the weekend with her much younger boyfriend Spike and an
 nounces she's selling the place. Rivalry\, regret\, and a costume party fo
 llow. The play won the 2013 Tony Award for Best Play\; this production com
 es from Arcadia Theater.
GEO:34.0765277;-84.2884766
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Arcadia Theater\, 180 Academy St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.simpletix.com/e/vanya-sasha-masha-spike-tickets-279857
END:VEVENT
