BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Macbeth
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T164500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1475@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's Scottish tragedy of witches\, prophecy\, and a c
 ouple who won't wait for fate\, from the Atlanta Shakespeare Company.\n\nT
 hree witches hail a victorious Scottish general as a future king\, and he 
 and his wife decide not to leave the crown to chance. Shakespeare's shorte
 st tragedy traces their climb from prophecy to murder to guilt that will n
 ot wash off. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company\, performed with food an
 d drink served at your table. A 2025 Suzi Bass Awards Recommended Show.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/macbeth
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Cadillac Crew
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T170000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-470@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Tori Sampson's drama: four activists in a Virginia civil right
 s office ask whether the movement's equality includes women.\n\nTori Samps
 on's play unfolds in a Virginia civil rights office on the day of a much-a
 nticipated Rosa Parks speech\, where four activists start asking whether t
 he movement's promise of equality extends to women. It reclaims the storie
 s of the overlooked organizers behind desegregation\, with more humor than
  the setup suggests. Karlotta Washington directs for the Conyers Rockdale 
 Council for the Arts. Runs through October 25.
GEO:33.6671075;-84.0180229
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Conyers Rockdale Council for the Arts\, 910 Center St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://conyersarts.org/calender-of-events/cadillac-crew/var/ri-2.l-L1
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Frankenstein: The Monster Play
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T171500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1202@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Mary Shelley's gothic tale onstage: a scientist\, the creature
  he abandons\, and the reckoning between them.\n\nA stage adaptation of Ma
 ry Shelley's 1818 novel. Victor Frankenstein stitches life together from t
 he dead\, recoils from what he's made\, and flees\; the abandoned creature
 \, left to learn the world alone\, goes looking for his maker. From Pumpho
 use Players\, one of Georgia's oldest continuously operating community the
 atres\, performing in a 70-seat house where nobody sits far from the monst
 er.
GEO:34.1644344;-84.7971239
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Pumphouse Players\, 114 W Main St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/frankenstein-the-monster-play-tickets-198
 9768069860
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Other Paths To God
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T191500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-579@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Five ICU nurses\, $3 million missing\, one scandal: a world-pr
 emiere comedy from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith.\n\nA world premiere 
 from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith\, writer of The Wash. When $3 milli
 on goes missing at Morey Medical Center and fingers point at the ICU's fiv
 e nurses\, everybody's worst behavior comes out. Smith drew on interviews 
 with real Atlanta nurses to write about what it means to give your life to
  a job that doesn't love you back. Commissioned through Horizon Theatre's 
 Black Women Speak program\; runs through November 8.
GEO:33.7620155;-84.3525137
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Horizon Theatre\, 1083 Austin Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.horizontheatre.com/144305/145633
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jeffrey Hatcher's The Turn of the Screw
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261028T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261028T210000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1476@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Two actors\, one piano\, and Henry James's ghost story perform
 ed in the round — no intermission\, one week only.\n\nJeffrey Hatcher's 
 adaptation of Henry James's 1898 novella: a new governess arrives at an En
 glish manor and begins seeing ghosts around the children in her care\, inc
 luding the specter of the woman who held the job before her. Whether the h
 auntings are real or her own fevered invention is the question the play ke
 eps turning. Two actors carry the whole story\, performed in the round wit
 h live atmospheric piano. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company\; a one-wee
 k run with no intermission and no latecomer seating.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/jeffrey-hatchers-th
 e-turn-of-the-screw
END:VEVENT
