 slike." Robby Myles directs for Authenticity Theater. Runs through October
  31.
GEO:33.7639125;-84.3509364
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:7 Stages Theatre\, 1105 Euclid Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://authenticitytheater.ludus.com/index.php?sections=events
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Vanya and Sonia and Masha and Spike
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261101T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261101T160000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1265@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Christopher Durang's Chekhov-riffing comedy: a movie-star sist
 er\, her young boyfriend\, and a family farmhouse up for sale.\n\nChristop
 her Durang's comedy borrows its names and its moods from Chekhov\, then le
 ts them loose in present-day Pennsylvania. Siblings Vanya and Sonia have s
 pent their quiet lives in the family farmhouse\; their movie-star sister M
 asha blows in for the weekend with her much younger boyfriend Spike and an
 nounces she's selling the place. Rivalry\, regret\, and a costume party fo
 llow. The play won the 2013 Tony Award for Best Play\; this production com
 es from Arcadia Theater.
GEO:34.0765277;-84.2884766
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Arcadia Theater\, 180 Academy St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.simpletix.com/e/vanya-sasha-masha-spike-tickets-279857
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Other Paths To God
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261101T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261101T191500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-585@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Five ICU nurses\, $3 million missing\, one scandal: a world-pr
 emiere comedy from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith.\n\nA world premiere 
 from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith\, writer of The Wash. When $3 milli
 on goes missing at Morey Medical Center and fingers point at the ICU's fiv
 e nurses\, everybody's worst behavior comes out. Smith drew on interviews 
 with real Atlanta nurses to write about what it means to give your life to
  a job that doesn't love you back. Commissioned through Horizon Theatre's 
 Black Women Speak program\; runs through November 8.
GEO:33.7620155;-84.3525137
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Horizon Theatre\, 1083 Austin Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.horizontheatre.com/144305/145634
END:VEVENT
