BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Miracle on 34th Street
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261106T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261106T223000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-712@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:The 1947 Christmas classic on stage: a department-store Santa 
 who insists he is the real thing.\n\nA stage adaptation of the 1947 holida
 y classic. When the Macy's Thanksgiving Parade Santa shows up drunk\, a wh
 ite-bearded old man named Kris Kringle steps in as a last-minute replaceme
 nt — and turns out to be so convincing that every child believes him\, n
 ot least because he claims to actually be Santa Claus. Along the way he wo
 rks on the toughest cases in New York: a cynical\, divorced single mother 
 and her fairy-tale-proof six-year-old daughter. From the Players Guild at 
 Sugar Hill\, a Gwinnett County community theatre company.
GEO:34.1070667;-84.0353528
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:The Eagle Theater\, 5029 W Broad St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/36627/performance/11797887/selecttickets
END:VEVENT
