DESCRIPTION:The 1947 holiday classic on stage: a department-store Santa wh
 o insists he's the real thing.\n\nA stage version of the 1947 film about K
 ris Kringle\, an old man hired to play Santa at Macy's who calmly maintain
 s that he is Santa — a claim that eventually lands him in a New York cou
 rtroom with his sanity on trial. Between the skeptical single mother who h
 ired him and her even more skeptical young daughter\, the question of beli
 eving becomes the whole ballgame. From Southside Theatre Guild\, an all-vo
 lunteer community theatre running since 1973.
GEO:33.5672762;-84.5821546
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Southside Theatre Guild\, 20 W Campbellton St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tockify.com/stgevents/detail/1020/1794166200000
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Othello
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261108T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261108T164500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1481@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's tragedy of jealousy — Iago whispers\, and a gr
 eat general's faith in his wife unravels.\n\nShakespeare's tragedy of a Ve
 netian general undone not by war but by his own ensign: Iago\, passed over
  for promotion\, sets out to convince Othello that his new wife Desdemona 
 has been unfaithful\, using little more than insinuation and a misplaced h
 andkerchief. Iago is one of the longest roles in the canon\, and watching 
 him work the room is half the horror. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company
 \, performed Elizabethan-style with food and drink served at your table.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/othello
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Miracle on 34th Street
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261108T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261108T173000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-715@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:The 1947 Christmas classic on stage: a department-store Santa 
 who insists he is the real thing.\n\nA stage adaptation of the 1947 holida
 y classic. When the Macy's Thanksgiving Parade Santa shows up drunk\, a wh
 ite-bearded old man named Kris Kringle steps in as a last-minute replaceme
 nt — and turns out to be so convincing that every child believes him\, n
 ot least because he claims to actually be Santa Claus. Along the way he wo
 rks on the toughest cases in New York: a cynical\, divorced single mother 
 and her fairy-tale-proof six-year-old daughter. From the Players Guild at 
 Sugar Hill\, a Gwinnett County community theatre company.
GEO:34.1070667;-84.0353528
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:The Eagle Theater\, 5029 W Broad St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/36627/performance/11797892/selecttickets
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:It's a Wonderful Life: A Live Radio Play
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261108T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261108T171500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-946@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Capra's 1946 Christmas classic restaged as a live 1940s radio 
 broadcast\, with onstage foley effects and actors doubling dozens of roles
 .\n\nThe story of George Bailey\, the Bedford Falls building-and-loan man 
 who hits bottom one snowy Christmas Eve and gets shown what his town would
  look like if he'd never been born. This adaptation of Frank Capra's 1946 
 film plays out as a period radio broadcast: a small ensemble at vintage mi
 crophones voicing dozens of characters\, with every footstep\, door slam\,
  and ringing bell made live by a foley artist in full view. Presented by T
 he Strand Theatre.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 06WSKHMA4
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Other Paths To God
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261108T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261108T191500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-591@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Five ICU nurses\, $3 million missing\, one scandal: a world-pr
 emiere comedy from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith.\n\nA world premiere 
 from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith\, writer of The Wash. When $3 milli
 on goes missing at Morey Medical Center and fingers point at the ICU's fiv
 e nurses\, everybody's worst behavior comes out. Smith drew on interviews 
 with real Atlanta nurses to write about what it means to give your life to
  a job that doesn't love you back. Commissioned through Horizon Theatre's 
 Black Women Speak program\; runs through November 8.
GEO:33.7620155;-84.3525137
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Horizon Theatre\, 1083 Austin Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.horizontheatre.com/144305/145635
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Other Desert Cities
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261108T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261108T191500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1148@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Jon Robin Baitz's Pulitzer-finalist family drama: a daughter's
  tell-all memoir detonates a Palm Springs Christmas.\n\nJon Robin Baitz's 
 drama\, a finalist for the 2012 Pulitzer Prize\, unfolds over Christmas Ev
 e 2004 in Palm Springs. Brooke Wyeth comes home after six years away with 
 a finished memoir that digs into the death of her brother\, a chapter her 
 staunchly Republican parents have spent decades keeping closed. Her aunt S
 ilda\, fresh from rehab and firmly on the other side of the political fenc
 e\, is also in the house. The festive reunion turns into a fight over memo
 ry\, loyalty\, and who gets to tell the family's story. Presented by Merel
 y Players.
GEO:33.9031178;-84.2776526
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Merely Players Presents\, 3785 King Ave
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.merelyplayerspresents.com/event-details/other-desert-citie
 s-2026-11-08-17-00
END:VEVENT
