SUMMARY:The Last Gift
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261122T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261122T160000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1692@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:World-premiere Christmas play about a crotchety nursing-home r
 esident and the young child who wins him over.\n\nA new play set in a nurs
 ing home around the Christmas holidays\, where a young child works on the 
 defenses of a crotchety old man. Atlanta playwright Earnest Lewis\, also a
  children's book author\, wrote it\, weaving in elder care\, adoption\, lo
 neliness\, and family. Dave Di Pietro directs this world premiere for the 
 Conyers Rockdale Council for the Arts. Runs through November 22.
GEO:33.6671075;-84.0180229
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Conyers Rockdale Council for the Arts\, 910 Center St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
