 eat general's faith in his wife unravels.\n\nShakespeare's tragedy of a Ve
 netian general undone not by war but by his own ensign: Iago\, passed over
  for promotion\, sets out to convince Othello that his new wife Desdemona 
 has been unfaithful\, using little more than insinuation and a misplaced h
 andkerchief. Iago is one of the longest roles in the canon\, and watching 
 him work the room is half the horror. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company
 \, performed Elizabethan-style with food and drink served at your table.
