SUMMARY:At All Cost
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261128T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261128T150000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1693@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:A drama about Black WWII veterans denied their promised GI Bil
 l benefits\, presented by Conyers Rockdale Council for the Arts.\n\nA dram
 a following a Black soldier home from World War II\, where the GI Bill's p
 romises of housing\, education\, and opportunity quietly evaporate at the 
 point of delivery. The play traces how that denial rippled through generat
 ions of Black families in America. Presented by the Conyers Rockdale Counc
 il for the Arts\, with artistic director Rashida Costa among the cast.
GEO:33.6671075;-84.0180229
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Conyers Rockdale Council for the Arts\, 910 Center St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://conyersarts.org/calender-of-events/at-all-cost/
END:VEVENT
