BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:It's a Wonderful Life: A Live Radio Play
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261205T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261205T214500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1155@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Joe Landry's radio-play staging of the 1946 Capra classic\, co
 mplete with live foley sound effects and music.\n\nJoe Landry's adaptation
  reframes the 1946 Frank Capra film as a 1940s radio broadcast: a small en
 semble of actors plays every citizen of Bedford Falls\, with sound effects
  and music made live on stage. The story is the one you know from the movi
 e\, where George Bailey hits bottom on Christmas Eve and an angel shows hi
 m what the town would look like if he had never been born. From Merely Pla
 yers\, and family-friendly.
GEO:33.9031178;-84.2776526
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Merely Players Presents\, 3785 King Ave
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.merelyplayerspresents.com/event-details/its-a-wonderful-li
 fe-a-live-radio-play-2026-12-05-19-30
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Charles Dickens' A Christmas Carol
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261205T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261205T213500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1495@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Dickens' ghost story told by a handful of actors\, with song\,
  an Atlanta Shakespeare Company holiday tradition of 20-plus years.\n\nJ. 
 Tony Brown's adaptation of Dickens' 1843 novella\, a fixture of the Atlant
 a Shakespeare Company's December calendar for more than two decades\, this
  year in a staging by Kati Grace Kirby. The approach is storytelling rathe
 r than spectacle: a small group of performers\, with a bit of song\, follo
 ws the miser Ebenezer Scrooge from his counting house through a Christmas 
 Eve visited by three ghosts and a certain small boy named Tiny Tim. The pl
 ayhouse's dinner-table seating means food and drink arrive during the perf
 ormance.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/charles-dickens-a-c
 hristmas-carol
END:VEVENT
