BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Dickens Christmas
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261213T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261213T164500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-449@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:A farce about a theatre troupe's disastrous attempt to stage A
  Christmas Carol\, back for a second year.\n\nNot A Christmas Carol itself
 \, but a comedy about trying to perform it: an earnest theatre troupe take
 s on the Dickens classic and everything that can go wrong does\, from blow
 n cues to full-scale onstage disasters. The holiday warmth survives the wr
 eckage\, more or less. From Cherokee Theatre\, returning for a second year
 \, and suitable for all ages.
GEO:34.2365417;-84.4902423
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Canton Theatre\, 171 E Main St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/cherokeetheatre/1960/event/1465856
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Charles Dickens' A Christmas Carol
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261213T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261213T163500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1500@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Dickens' ghost story told by a handful of actors\, with song\,
  an Atlanta Shakespeare Company holiday tradition of 20-plus years.\n\nJ. 
 Tony Brown's adaptation of Dickens' 1843 novella\, a fixture of the Atlant
 a Shakespeare Company's December calendar for more than two decades\, this
  year in a staging by Kati Grace Kirby. The approach is storytelling rathe
 r than spectacle: a small group of performers\, with a bit of song\, follo
 ws the miser Ebenezer Scrooge from his counting house through a Christmas 
 Eve visited by three ghosts and a certain small boy named Tiny Tim. The pl
 ayhouse's dinner-table seating means food and drink arrive during the perf
 ormance.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/charles-dickens-a-c
 hristmas-carol
END:VEVENT
