DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1515@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's Beatrice and Benedick trade insults until their 
 friends trick them into love\, from the Atlanta Shakespeare Company.\n\nSh
 akespeare's comedy of two committed singles: Beatrice and Benedick spar so
  relentlessly that their friends conspire to make each believe the other i
 s secretly in love. Meanwhile the villainous Don John schemes to wreck the
  wedding of the young lovers Claudio and Hero. From the Atlanta Shakespear
 e Company\, performed Elizabethan-style with table seating and food and dr
 ink service during the show. A 2026 Suzi Bass Awards Recommended Show.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
