BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sweat
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270205T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270205T213000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1390@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Lynn Nottage's Pulitzer-winning drama of factory friends in a 
 Rust Belt bar as the layoffs begin.\n\nLynn Nottage's 2015 drama\, winner 
 of the 2017 Pulitzer Prize\, set mostly in a bar in Reading\, Pennsylvania
 \, where a circle of steel-plant workers has gathered for years. When one 
 of the friends is promoted to management and jobs start moving to Mexico\,
  the lines between labor and boss\, and along race\, begin to cut through 
 the group. Nottage built the play from years of interviews with residents 
 of Reading\, then one of the poorest cities in America. From the Henry Pla
 yers.
GEO:33.4486439;-84.1418279
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:The Henry Players Theater\, 136 Hood St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.simpletix.com/e/sweat-tickets-271676
END:VEVENT
