BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Romance Repertory: Romeo and Juliet and Much Ado About Nothing
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270214T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270214T194000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1521@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:This performance is Romeo and Juliet\, half of a repertory pai
 ring Shakespeare's tragedy with Much Ado About Nothing.\n\nTwo Shakespeare
  plays about love\, running in repertory from the Atlanta Shakespeare Comp
 any. This performance is Romeo and Juliet: two teenagers fall for each oth
 er across a family feud\, with one well-intentioned Friar trying to hold i
 t all together. Kelly Criss directs the company's 23rd anniversary product
 ion of the tragedy. On alternate dates\, Alejandra Ruiz directs Much Ado A
 bout Nothing\, the Beatrice-and-Benedick comedy of two confirmed singles t
 oo witty for their own good. Table seating with food and drink service dur
 ing the show\; the repertory runs through February 28.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/the-romance-reperto
 ry-romeo-and-juliet-and-much-ado-about-nothing
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Proof
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270214T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270214T170000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1629@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:David Auburn's Pulitzer-winning drama: a mathematician's daugh
 ter\, a mysterious proof\, and the question of who wrote it.\n\nDavid Aubu
 rn's drama won the 2001 Pulitzer Prize and the Tony for Best Play. Catheri
 ne spent years caring for her father\, a brilliant University of Chicago m
 athematician whose mind unraveled before his death. Now one of his former 
 students is combing through the hundred-odd notebooks he left behind\, and
  a groundbreaking proof about prime numbers surfaces. The question of who 
 wrote it forces Catherine to reckon with how much of her father\, genius a
 nd instability alike\, she may have inherited. From Stage Door Theatre.
GEO:33.9447222;-84.3319444
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Stage Door Theatre\, 5339 Chamblee Dunwoody Rd
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/36385/performance/11825815/selecttickets
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Little Women
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270214T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270214T173000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-727@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Alcott's four March sisters grow up\, in Thomas Hischak's stag
 e adaptation from Players Guild at Sugar Hill.\n\nLouisa May Alcott's nove
 l of the four March sisters — headstrong Jo\, practical Meg\, gentle Bet
 h\, and ambitious Amy — coming of age in Civil War-era New England\, eac
 h chasing a different idea of what her life should be. Thomas Hischak's st
 age adaptation\, from Players Guild at Sugar Hill.
GEO:34.1070667;-84.0353528
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:The Eagle Theater\, 5029 W Broad St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/36627/performance/11797900/selecttickets
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Time Stands Still
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270214T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270214T171500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1206@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Donald Margulies's drama of a war photographer home from Iraq\
 , deciding whether she can want an ordinary life.\n\nSarah\, a photojourna
 list\, is back in Brooklyn after a roadside bomb in Iraq nearly killed her
 . Her boyfriend James\, a reporter who left the assignment before it happe
 ned\, carries the guilt. A visit from an old friend and his much younger n
 ew girlfriend sharpens the question of whether the couple can trade the fr
 ont lines for something conventional. Donald Margulies's play earned a Ton
 y nomination for Best Play\, with the New York Daily News praising its "in
 telligence and humor." From Pumphouse Players\, staged in a 70-seat conver
 ted 1940s cinema.
GEO:34.1644344;-84.7971239
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Pumphouse Players\, 114 W Main St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/time-stands-still-tickets-1989768541270
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Miseducated
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270216T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270216T214500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-250@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:New play from Brandon P. Fleming's memoir: Atlanta debate stud
 ents\, and a coach arguing with the universe itself.\n\nRudi Goblen adapts
  Brandon P. Fleming's memoir into a world premiere commissioned by the All
 iance Theatre. Atlanta high schoolers train for an elite Harvard debate pr
 ogram under a coach who demands they sharpen every argument. Then Brandon 
 gets pulled into a surreal debate of his own\, arguing with the universe o
 ver the memories that made him and whether a life can be rewritten. Teo Ca
 stellanos directs\, with the story told through debate rounds\, music\, an
 d spoken word. Runs through February 21.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164246/164539
END:VEVENT
