  a groundbreaking proof about prime numbers surfaces. The question of who 
 wrote it forces Catherine to reckon with how much of her father\, genius a
 nd instability alike\, she may have inherited. From Stage Door Theatre.
GEO:33.9447222;-84.3319444
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Stage Door Theatre\, 5339 Chamblee Dunwoody Rd
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/36385/performance/11825816/selecttickets
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Time Stands Still
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270221T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270221T171500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1209@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Donald Margulies's drama of a war photographer home from Iraq\
 , deciding whether she can want an ordinary life.\n\nSarah\, a photojourna
 list\, is back in Brooklyn after a roadside bomb in Iraq nearly killed her
 . Her boyfriend James\, a reporter who left the assignment before it happe
 ned\, carries the guilt. A visit from an old friend and his much younger n
 ew girlfriend sharpens the question of whether the couple can trade the fr
 ont lines for something conventional. Donald Margulies's play earned a Ton
 y nomination for Best Play\, with the New York Daily News praising its "in
 telligence and humor." From Pumphouse Players\, staged in a 70-seat conver
 ted 1940s cinema.
GEO:34.1644344;-84.7971239
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Pumphouse Players\, 114 W Main St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/time-stands-still-tickets-1989768541270
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Miseducated
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270221T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270221T214500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-257@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:New play from Brandon P. Fleming's memoir: Atlanta debate stud
 ents\, and a coach arguing with the universe itself.\n\nRudi Goblen adapts
  Brandon P. Fleming's memoir into a world premiere commissioned by the All
 iance Theatre. Atlanta high schoolers train for an elite Harvard debate pr
 ogram under a coach who demands they sharpen every argument. Then Brandon 
 gets pulled into a surreal debate of his own\, arguing with the universe o
 ver the memories that made him and whether a life can be rewritten. Teo Ca
 stellanos directs\, with the story told through debate rounds\, music\, an
 d spoken word. Runs through February 21.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164246/164544
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:What the Constitution Means to Me
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270224T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270224T213000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1082@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Heidi Schreck's Tony-nominated play revisiting her teenage Con
 stitution-debate speeches\, in its Atlanta premiere.\n\nHeidi Schreck put 
 herself through college giving prize-winning speeches about the Constituti
 on at American Legion halls\; her 2019 Broadway play returns to those cont
 ests\, toggling between her fifteen-year-old self and the woman she became
 . What starts as a debate exercise opens into the stories of the women in 
 her family and how the document actually treated them — funny\, personal
 \, and pointed by turns. A Tony nominee for Best Play and a Pulitzer final
 ist\, it gets its Atlanta premiere from Theatrical Outfit.
GEO:33.757035;-84.389486
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Theatrical Outfit\, 84 Luckie St NW
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Women of Willow Creek
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270224T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270224T213000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1703@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Six women\, 28 days\, one rehabilitation facility: a drama of 
 recovery from Merely Players.\n\nA drama that follows Harper and five othe
 r women through a 28-day stay in a rehabilitation facility\, their recover
 ies tangled together as the days count down. The subject matter is heavy a
 nd unflinching — suicide\, eating disorders\, self-harm\, substance use\
 , and PTSD all figure in — but the play finds real humor in the darkest 
 corners of the ward. From Merely Players\, a small non-equity company that
  stages work reflecting its community's diversity.
GEO:33.9031178;-84.2776526
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Merely Players Presents\, 3785 King Ave
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.merelyplayerspresents.com/event-details/the-women-of-willo
 w-creek-02-24-26
END:VEVENT
