BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Arcadia
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270522T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270522T221500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1220@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Tom Stoppard's 1993 comedy of chaos theory\, Byron gossip\, an
 d one country house across two centuries.\n\nTom Stoppard's 1993 play unfo
 lds in a single English country-house room across two centuries. In 1809\,
  teenage math prodigy Thomasina Coverly scribbles ideas decades ahead of h
 er time while her tutor dodges a duel over another man's wife. In the pres
 ent day\, two rival academics comb the same house for evidence of a scanda
 l involving Lord Byron\, and keep getting the past wrong. One 1993 critic 
 grumbled it was 'too clever by about two-and-three-quarters'\; many others
  rank it as Stoppard's finest play. From Pumphouse Players.
GEO:34.1644344;-84.7971239
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Pumphouse Players\, 114 W Main St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/arcadia-tickets-1989768662633
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:John Proctor is the Villain
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270523T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270523T161500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-336@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Kimberly Belflower's Tony-nominated comedy-drama: Georgia teen
 s study The Crucible and start doubting its hero.\n\nAn English class in a
  one-stoplight Georgia town takes up The Crucible\, and the students begin
  to suspect Arthur Miller's hero isn't the good guy after all. Kimberly Be
 lflower's play mixes pop music\, first crushes\, and feminist fury into wh
 at The New York Times called a "vital\, hilarious\, [and] thrilling" portr
 ait of teenage girlhood. After a 2025 Broadway run that earned seven Tony 
 nominations\, including Best Play\, it makes its Georgia debut from the Al
 liance Theatre\, directed by Autumn Angelettie. Runs through June 6.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164234/164354
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Children
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270523T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270523T163000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1045@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Lucy Kirkwood's darkly comic thriller: two retired nuclear phy
 sicists\, a colleague back after 38 years\, and old debts coming due.\n\nI
 n a cottage on the British coast\, two married\, retired nuclear physicist
 s live quietly in the wake of a disaster. Then a former colleague reappear
 s after 38 years\, and the couple's careful equilibrium starts to crack. L
 ucy Kirkwood's 2016 thriller\, funnier than its premise suggests\, asks wh
 at one generation owes the one that follows\; it was a hit in London and o
 n Broadway\, and in 2019 Guardian writers ranked it third among the greate
 st theatrical works since 2000. Presented by Theatrical Outfit.
GEO:33.757035;-84.389486
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Theatrical Outfit\, 84 Luckie St NW
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Mama Bear Repertory: The Winter's Tale and Mel Konner’s Sixt
 een Springs or Four Loves
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270523T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270523T164500
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1571@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's late romance in repertory with a new Atlanta pla
 y filling in its sixteen-year gap.\n\nA repertory pairing from the Atlanta
  Shakespeare Company: Shakespeare's rarely staged late romance alongside a
  brand-new companion piece. In The Winter's Tale\, a king's unfounded jeal
 ousy costs him his wife\, his children\, and his best friend before the st
 ory thaws into pastoral comedy and magic. On alternating dates\, Sixteen S
 prings or Four Loves\, by Atlanta playwright Mel Konner\, dramatizes the s
 ixteen years Shakespeare skips: the abandoned princess raised by shepherds
 \, and Antigonus surviving his famous bear. The repertory runs through May
  30.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/the-mama-bear-reper
 tory-the-winters-tale-and-mel-konner-s-sixteen-springs-or-four-loves
END:VEVENT
