  one-stoplight Georgia town takes up The Crucible\, and the students begin
  to suspect Arthur Miller's hero isn't the good guy after all. Kimberly Be
 lflower's play mixes pop music\, first crushes\, and feminist fury into wh
 at The New York Times called a "vital\, hilarious\, [and] thrilling" portr
 ait of teenage girlhood. After a 2025 Broadway run that earned seven Tony 
 nominations\, including Best Play\, it makes its Georgia debut from the Al
 liance Theatre\, directed by Autumn Angelettie. Runs through June 6.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
