BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Every Brilliant Thing
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270814T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270814T213000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-1645@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Duncan Macmillan's one-performer play about a list of things w
 orth living for\, with the audience holding pieces of it.\n\nDuncan Macmil
 lan and Jonny Donahoe's one-performer play about a narrator who\, at age s
 even\, responds to his mother's suicide attempt by starting a list of ever
 ything worth living for. The list grows through college\, marriage\, and a
  depression of his own. The audience keeps the show running: some hold num
 bered cards and shout out entries on cue (rollercoasters\, people falling 
 over)\, and a few get drafted into roles on the spot. From Stage Door Thea
 tre.
GEO:33.9447222;-84.3319444
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Stage Door Theatre\, 5339 Chamblee Dunwoody Rd
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/36385/performance/11825838/selecttickets
END:VEVENT
