BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Death of a Salesman
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270908T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270908T220000
DTSTAMP:20260707T064157Z
UID:occ-969@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Arthur Miller's 1949 Pulitzer-winning tragedy of Willy Loman\,
  a salesman whose dreams keep outrunning his life.\n\nArthur Miller's 1949
  tragedy\, told through the memories\, dreams\, and arguments of Willy Lom
 an\, an aging traveling salesman who wants greatness for himself and his s
 ons and cannot square that want with the life he actually has. It won both
  the Pulitzer Prize for Drama and the Tony for Best Play\; the Daily Teleg
 raph called it the most perceptive and moving play America had produced in
  a long time. The closing production of Theatrical Outfit's 50th anniversa
 ry season. Runs through September 30.
GEO:33.757035;-84.389486
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T063344Z
LOCATION:Theatrical Outfit\, 84 Luckie St NW
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
